			<h3 id="birger_haarbrandt">Birger Haarbrandt (Germany)</h3>
			<table class="TableInvisible">
			<tbody>
			<tr>
				<td><img width="113" src="/files/about/birger_haarbrandt.jpg"></td>
				<td>
				<p>Birger Haarbrandt holds a B.A. in Medical Information Management and an M.Sc. in Computer Science. Between 2013 and 2017, Birger has established the <a href="https://plri.de/en/forschung/projekte/hannover-medical-school-translational-research-framework-hamstr">Hannover Medical School Translational Research Framework (HaMSTR)</a>, investigating the enhancement of traditional data warehousing approaches (including i2b2/tranSMART) with openEHR.  He previously worked on the establishment of a regional health network in the state of Lower-Saxony based on IHE XDS and as a software developer for CGM MEDISTAR.</p>
				<p>Since 2015, he has substantially contributed to the concept of the <a href="http://www.highmed.org/">HiGHmed consortium</a> to apply for the <a href="http://www.medizininformatik-initiative.de/en/about-initiative">Medical Informatics Initiative</a>, a national research project to enable secondary use of health data across institutions.  Since the start of the project in January 2018, he is working in HiGHmed as a software architect for the <a href="https://plri.de/en">Peter L. Reichertz Institute for Medical Informatics</a>, aiming at the establishment of an open platform based on IHE, openEHR and FHIR between eight German university hospitals.</p>
				</td>
			</tr>
